From 1f813fb44087393043e14d7aac9314ddabe69c62 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mia Gorceva <elena@mite.club>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 13:24:25 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add machine Telegram bot module (MachineBot)

New module MachineBot.lsf (REQUIRE Mite, Telegram) implementing the
machine departure/arrival bot per organization:

- Machine identity: mark, machineNumber, tgUsername, tgChatId on Location
- botAccount per Organization (telegram account holding the token)
- generateMachineRoutes: morning departure/arrival = planned +-30 min,
  without overwriting real driver times
- sendMachineRoute(s): send '<number>1'/'<number>2' to the bot exactly like
  a driver would; sendMachineMsg captures telegram message_id, deleteMachineMsg
  removes the auto-message once the real driver message arrives
- WHEN on incoming Message: parse '47501'/'4750-1'/'4750 1' (strip separators,
  last digit = action 1|2, rest = number), find the machine, record the real
  departure/arrival, delete the bot's auto-message, mark processed

Mite.lsf: add ABSTRACT botRouteTimeFrom/botRouteTimeTo and put them first in
the routeTimeFrom/To OVERRIDE chain, so the route report uses the bot time
(real driver time if available, else generated, else planned).

lsfusion.properties: topModule = MachineBot (so the new module loads).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
